SystemBack-image
======================

Add imges created using Systemback (Software like Remastersys) to PXE Server

# mount /dev/cdrom /media

# mkdir /FTP/systemback-ubuntu
# cp -ar /media/* /FTP/systemback-ubuntu
# cp -ar /media/.disk /FTP/systemback-ubuntu

# umount /media 


# mkdir -p /var/lib/tftpboot/images/systemback-ubuntu
# cp -ar /FTP/systemback-ubuntu/casper/initrd.gz /var/lib/tftpboot/images/systemback-ubuntu
# cp -ar /FTP/systemback-ubuntu/casper/vmlinuz /var/lib/tftpboot/images/systemback-ubuntu


# vi /var/lib/tftpboot/pxelinux.cfg/default
......
#######Systemback-Ubuntu####################
LABEL SystemBack-Ubuntu14.04-Desktop
KERNEL images/systemback-ubuntu/vmlinuz
append boot=casper netboot=nfs nfsroot=100.0.0.11:/FTP/systemback-ubuntu/ initrd=images/systemback-ubuntu/initrd.gz finstall quiet splash
#

# vi /etc/exports
...
/FTP/systemback-ubuntu 100.0.0.0/24(ro,sync)
#

# exportfs -a
